<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
Differing from var. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium longiflorum var. brownii" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="longiflorum" variety="brownii">Lilium longiflorum brownii</taxonomicName>
by the greenish colouration on the outside of the corolla. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Lilium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lilium wenshanense" order="Liliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wenshanense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Lilium wenshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was differentiated by having articulated scales, a feature now found to vary across the range of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
